Shell Deer Park Risk Management Program Executive Summary
The location has a long-standing commitment to our workers, public safety and the environment.  This commitment is demonstrated by the amount of resources invested in accident prevention, such as training of personnel and considering safety in the design, installation, operation, and maintenance of our processes.  The below provides a brief description of the facility Risk Management Program.
(a)	The accidental release prevention and emergency response policies at the stationary source;
Our policy is to implement controls to prevent foreseeable releases or catastrophic incidents involving regulated substances and adhere to all applicable Federal, State and local rules and regulations.  Our location HSSE Commitment and Policy Statement mirrors our corporate guidelines to address such matters and is signed by the facility General Manager. As part of this commitment, the location has established a management system to help ensure safe operation of the processes at this facility that includes the prevention of accidental releases of hazardous substances.  One component of this system is a risk management program (RMP) that provides a basis for managing risks at the site.  The RMP complies with requirements of the Environmental Protection Agency¿s (EPA¿s) regulation 40 CFR part. 
(b)	The stationary source and regulated substances handled;
The location is located in Deer Park, Texas along the Houston Ship Channel some 20 miles east of downtown Houston.  The Shell Chemical LP facility manufactures base chemicals for sale to other chemical companies that transform them into other consumer products ranging from plastics to building materials.  
